shared_text:
Hospitality House food pantry
August 24 at 5:25 PM ·

A big thank you to Walled Lake Consolidated School District’s Walled Lake Central class of 2020. They took their prom money, close to $9,000, and decided to donate it to the community. They selected Hospitality House. What a wonderful show of support and generosity during these challenging times. Our futures are in good hands.

post_text: Thank you so much to those who have supported the Foundation for Excellence - Walled Lake Schools. Together we are "Acing Education in Walled Lake Schools.” If you are able to make a donation to the Foundation please consider it, they do great work for our learning community.
shared_text:
Foundation for Excellence - Walled Lake Schools
July 7 at 3:09 PM ·

Signs posted today, July 7th, at the offices of the Walled Lake Consolidated School District on Maple Rd. as we proudly share with our community support for "Acing Education," fundraiser replacing the Foundation's annual golf scramble.

PLATINUM SPONSOR: Auch Construction
SILVER SPONSOR: Community Financial Credit Union

BUSINESS SPONSORS: Arch Environmental, Dean Transportation, Edgenuity, Enviro-Clean, Hersh-Beattie-Isenberg, Hoekstra Transportation, Lusk Albertson, Peter Basso Associates, TMP Architecture, and Walled Lake Schools Federal Credit Union.

FRIENDS OF THE FOUNDATION: Walter Alix, John Babon, Foresight Design, Ken Gutman, Tom Holzer Ford, M3 Investment Services-Michelle Tomei, Morris-Phillips Philanthropic Funds, Royal Roofing, and David Steinberg.

OAKLANDCOUNTYBLOG.COM
Entries Now Open For ‘Oakland Together’ COVID-19 Safety Video & Art Contest

Oakland County, Michigan Government
July 8 at 6:40 PM ·

Share with us the importance of practicing #COVID19 safety in #OaklandCounty with our #OaklandTogether COVID-19 Safety Video & Visual Arts Contest. Residents ages 10 and up may submit a video or 2-D artwork showcasing COVID-19 safety by wearing a facial mask or practicing social distancing. http://ow.ly/NTyn50AtbR6

Submissions are due by Monday, July 20th at 11:59 p.m. For full contest details, visit: www.oakgov.com/covid/contests.

post_text:
The 2020 Michigan Week Community Awards Ceremony is a virtual version of the annual awards breakfast, honoring volunteers from throughout the Greater West Bloomfield area for their dedication and service to the community.

The Michigan Week Committee works year-round to plan and execute this event, and it is the friends, family, colleagues, and neighbors of the honorees whose nominations light the spark that leads to honoring our finest local volunteers.

This year's virtual ceremony is hosted by WWJ News Radio 950 and "The Splash's" Brooke Allen, and will be available on-demand at www.civiccentertv.com
